This article is a presidential memorandum issued by President Barack Obama on July 11, 2014. The memorandum delegates authority to the Secretary of State to carry out reporting functions outlined in section 4 of the Support for United States-Republic of Korea Civil Nuclear Cooperation Act. The President's authority to delegate this responsibility is derived from the Constitution and the laws of the United States. The memorandum also instructs the Secretary of State to publish the memorandum in the Federal Register.